title: ok, listen up pokemon gamers
body:
so, yknow how all the female protags in pokemon have good designs, right?

rosa for example:

dawn as well!:

however, my point here is that the male protags in pokemon look average at best.
weewoo weewoo, unpopular opinion alert but red, lucas, and elio are good examples of this. 

and what makes this worse is that in x/y, sun/moon, and ultra sun/moon, there are more customization options for the females than the males.

the male protag in x/y has  2,248,100 Poke worth of clothing. the female has  4,583,600 Poke worth. which, the female has twice as much clothing as the male

so, in conclusion:

please include more clothing and customization options for the male protagonist in pokemon sword and shield game freak

blog.name: pokemon-professor-sakura
blog.title: Asks: CLOSED! Submissions: OPEN!
blog.description:
(This is a roleplay blog run by @chickadee567)

((Talking out of character))

Hello there! I’m Professor Sakura, and I’m always willing

to help trainers and caretakers with their Pokemon.

You can ask me about Pokemon behavior, where certain Pokemon can be found,

and even report sightings of rare or mythical Pokemon.

((Search for the tag #rules to find rules for asks and submissions!))

question: Dragon?
answer:
• Turtonator (Fire/Dragon): Their Fire-type moves can counter any Ice-type opponents.
  • Dragalge (Poison/Dragon): Their Poison-type moves can counter any Fairy-type opponents.
  • Noivern (Flying/Dragon): Speedy boi.
  • Garchomp (Dragon/Ground): I have one! She’s very strong.
  • Goodra (Dragon): Tank. And also chonk.
  • Altaria (Dragon/Flying): I can’t resist the fluffiness.
